# REST API Best Practices

Follow these standards when adding or editing API routes. Reference: [src/app/api/v1/admin/events/route.ts](src/app/api/v1/admin/events/route.ts)

## URL and Versioning

- Use `/api/v1/` prefix for all routes
- Resource-based URLs: nouns only, no verbs
  - Good: `GET /api/v1/admin/programs`, `PATCH /api/v1/admin/messages/[id]`
  - Bad: `GET /api/get-programs`, `POST /api/admin/update-message`

## HTTP Status Codes

| Status | Use                           |
| ------ | ----------------------------- |
| 200    | Success (GET, PATCH, DELETE)  |
| 201    | Created (POST)                |
| 401    | Unauthenticated               |
| 403    | Authenticated but not allowed |
| 404    | Resource not found            |
| 422    | Validation error              |
| 429    | Rate limit exceeded           |
| 500    | Internal server error         |

## Response Structure

**Success (list):**

```typescript
return NextResponse.json({
  data: [...],
  meta: { page, limit, total, totalPages, hasMore }
});
```

**Success (single/create):**

```typescript
return NextResponse.json({ data: { ... }, meta: {} });
```

**Error:** Use `Errors` from `@/src/lib/api/errors`:

```typescript
import { Errors } from "@/src/lib/api/errors";

if (!params) return Errors.validation("Invalid query parameters", [...]);
if (!isAdmin) return Errors.unauthorized();
return Errors.tooManyRequests();
```

## Required Imports and Flow

```typescript
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { requireAdminSession } from "@/src/lib/admin/adminAuth";
import { Errors } from "@/src/lib/api/errors";
import { rateLimitMiddleware } from "@/src/lib/api/rateLimit";

export async function GET(req: NextRequest) {
  const { ok: rateOk, remaining } = rateLimitMiddleware(req);
  if (!rateOk) return Errors.tooManyRequests();

  const admin = await requireAdminSession();
  if (admin instanceof Response) return admin;

  // Validate query/body, then business logic
}
```

Admin routes: always call `requireAdminSession()` and return early if it returns a `Response`. Public routes: apply rate limiting only.

## Pagination, Filtering, Sorting

- List endpoints: support `?page=1&limit=20` (default limit 20, max 100)
- Filtering: `?search=`, `?programSlug=`, etc. as query params
- Sorting: `?sort=createdAt&order=asc|desc`

## Input Validation

- Validate all inputs: types, lengths, allowed values
- Return `Errors.validation(message, details)` with field-level details when invalid
- Apply length limits (e.g. string max 200, 500) to prevent abuse

## Naming Convention

- Use camelCase for JSON keys consistently
- Success: `data`, `meta`; Error: `error: { code, message, details? }`

## Security

- Rate limit: use `rateLimitMiddleware(req)` for admin and public routes
- Admin-only: enforce with `requireAdminSession()` before any data access
- Cron/webhooks: validate auth header (e.g. `NEXT_PUBLIC_CRON_SECRET`) instead of admin check
